R. E. HAMRICK and ANNIE B. HAMRICK, his wife, v. ELDRED NORTON and NATHAN NORTON. 11 So. (2nd) 475

January Term, 1942

January 22, 1943 Division B E. B. Donnell, for appellants. Errol S. Wiles, for appellees. PER CURIAM:

This cause having heretofore been submitted to the Court upon the transcript of the record of the final decree herein, and briefs of counsel for the respective parties; and the record having been seen and inspected, and the Court being now advised of its judgment to be given in the premises, it seems to the Court that there is no error in the said final decree; it is, therefore, considered, ordered and adjudged by the Court that the said final decree of the circuit court be, and the same is hereby affirmed.

Affirmed.

BUFORD, C. J., BROWN, THOMAS and SEBRING, JJ., concur.
